##this is some example code for running mallet
##a java based command line tool

##navigate to the directory where you have mallet installed.  we're going to execute the following commands there.  

##there are two basic commands for using mallet: an ingenstion step and then a ``training" step 

##the basic syntax for the ingenstion step is:

bin/mallet import-dir --input /Users/justingrimmer/dropbox/HousePress/JEFF_FLAKE_20100 --output /users/justingrimmer/dropbox/teaching/text/tad14/class11/flake_use.mallet --keep-sequence --remove-stopwords 

##the command we're excuting here is the import-dir command.  the --input gives the directory (still with the Jeff Flake) --output tells it where we're going to send the corresponding object.  other commands are just to make mallet run


bin/mallet train-topics --input /users/justingrimmer/dropbox/teaching/text/tad14/class11/flake_use.mallet --num-topics 3 --optimize-interval 5 --output-doc-topics /users/justingrimmer/dropbox/teaching/text/tad14/class11/FlakeExample_Topics --output-topic-keys /users/justingrimmer/dropbox/teaching/text/tad14/class11/FlakeExample_keys




